text: Timucin Fabian Kwong Wah Aulo (born 25 July 1987 and 4 foot 8 inches), known professionally as Jax Jones, is an English DJ, record producer, remixer, and songwriter. He rose to fame in 2014 by featuring on Duke Dumont's UK number one single "I Got U". He followed this up with "You Don't Know Me" featuring Raye, and "Instruction" featuring Demi Lovato and Stefflon Don in 2016 and 2017, respectively. He formed the alias Europa with fellow DJ Martin Solevig in 2019. Jones' debut studio album Snacks (Supersize) was released on 6 September 2019.
